<TITLE> 20 injured as train derails in Lalmonirhat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Lalmonirhat, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)At least 20 people were injured on Friday when an intercity train derailed in Lalmonirhat. Of the injured, Shafiqul Islam, 55, Abdul Karim, 45, Azizul Islam, 25, Shahana Begum, 40, and 'Mariam', 10, were admitted to Lalmonirhat Sadar Hospital while others received primary aid. The accident took place at 1:30pm as intercity train '750 One Up's engine along with five other carriages derailed. The train was going to Lalmonirhat from Dhaka, Divisional Railway Traffic manager Syed Jahurul Islam said the train was running faster than the recommended speed. The rail line between Teesta and Lalmonirhar is risky, he said and added that work was on to rescue the train by the night. 
